  "datePublished": "2025-03-29",
  "description": "The Moon drifts through Virgo today, in a waxing crescent phase that leaves more unsaid than revealed. Emotionally, there’s an impulse toward tidying—toward making sense of what frays and murmurs just beneath the surface. But this is not a time for finishing. The crescent insists on incompletion: it gestures toward clarity, but doesn’t grant it. What stirs inside may feel like a yearning for purification, but Virgo’s real gift lies not in purity, but in devotion—repetitive, imperfect, deeply embodied attention.\n",
